  "start_screen": {
    "tip_prefix": "Tip",
    "tips": [
      "Type /help when you inevitably forget everything.",
      "Shift+TAB cycles channels. Like flipping through regrets, but faster.",
      "Shift+Space changes the time period. Time travel, basically.",
      "/login \u003ccode\u003e — the door doesn't open for strangers.",
      "Every command starts with a slash. Like every argument starts with 'well actually'.",
      "Ctrl+K opens the palette. The K stands for 'knew you'd need this'.",
      "Your conversations save automatically. Your dignity does not.",
      "/new starts fresh. The past is a coward anyway.",
      "Your sub count is a number. Numbers don't love you back.",
      "Upload consistency beats talent. Talent didn't read this tip.",
      "The algorithm is not your friend. It is barely your acquaintance.",
      "Thumbnails sell. Your soul is optional but encouraged.",
      "Reply to comments. Even the unhinged ones. Especially those.",
      "A title is a promise. Break it and the watch time leaves.",
      "Retention is king. Your intro is the regicide.",
      "Post at the right time. There is no right time. Post anyway.",
      "Burnout is a metric too. Nobody graphs it. We should.",
      "Analytics tell a story. Usually a tragedy.",
      "CTR low? The thumbnail is gaslighting you.",
      "Shorts are a portal. To where, nobody knows.",
      "The 'Notify' bell is a lie we all agreed upon.",
      "Demonetization is just YouTube's way of saying 'spicy'.",
      "Your worst vid taught you more than your best.",
      "Niche down. Then down. Then keep going. Hit bedrock.",
      "Watch your watch time, not your watch.",
      "Collabs multiply reach and divide royalties.",
      "Copyright strikes: three and you're a folk legend.",
      "The comments section is undefeated. Wear a helmet.",
      "Caption your vids. The algorithm reads text, not minds.",
      "End screens: the polite way to beg.",
      "Trends die fast. So do channels that only chase them.",
      "/help is free. Therapy is not. We do what we can.",
      "A blank start screen is a canvas. Or a void. Depends on the day.",
      "Pin a comment. Assert dominance.",
      "Your intro is too long. Yes, that one. Cut it.",
      "Consistency is a personality trait you can fake with a calendar.",
      "Every viral vid is an accident wearing a suit.",
      "The 1,000 sub milestone is mostly your mom and bots.",
      "Tags barely matter. Use them anyway, like a lucky sock.",
      "Audio quality beats vid quality. People forgive ugly, not deaf.",
      "Cliffhangers boost retention. Resolve them eventually. Maybe.",
      "Premiere a vid. Watch nobody show up live. Character building.",
      "Your channel banner is older than some of your subs.",
      "The 'I'm not asking for much' subscribe pitch fools no one.",
      "Reupload? The algorithm has a long memory and a short temper.",
      "Schedule uploads. Future you is unreliable and you know it.",
      "Community posts: shouting into a slightly smaller void.",
      "The best time to start was years ago. The second best is now.",
      "Touch grass between uploads. The grass misses you.",
      "If all else fails, /help. If that fails too, blame Mercury."
    ]
